The paper deals with the topics of locally testable codes, linear codes, and list-decodable codes, which are all related to information theory and coding theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves combinatorial constructions and algorithms, which suggest cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the properties of codes, which may fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
